Method copyattr

copyattr( self, source, destination, stats=None )

Copies the attributes from source to destination, (re)using the given stats info if provided.

Method copydir

copydir( self, source, destination, path )

Copies the given directory to the destination. This does not copy its contents.

Method copyfile

copyfile( self, source, destination, path )

Copies the given file. This will check the file's inode to detect hardlink. If a file with the same inode has already been copied, then a hard link will be created to that file, otherwise a new file will be created.

Method copylink

copylink( self, source, destination, path )

Copies the given symlink to the destination. This preserves the target but does not check if it is valid or not.

Method fromCatalogue

fromCatalogue( self, path )

Reads the given catalogue and copies directories, symlinks and files listed in the catalogue. Note that this expects the catalogue to be in traversal order.
